{
  "texts": [
    "In conclusion, the findings of this study demonstrate that the Custom-CNN model accurately and rapidly identifies COVID-19 from chest X-ray images.",
    "To mitigate the risk of bias, a large dataset of COVID-19 cases was employed, and extensive preprocessing techniques were applied to ensure appropriate inputs to the CNN architecture.",
    "Figure 9 illustrates the training, validation accuracy, and validation loss for the different classes.",
    "In this figure, one may observe certain sudden small value changes (peaks) in the validation accuracy and validation loss.",
    "Such occurrences are common when there is a mismatch between the distribution or characteristics of the training and validation images."
  ]
}